{
  "stem": "747.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We-- others knew as much-- we find out that it was a group of women who were worked in they called a union-- in the leader union.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In Auschwitz proper was a munition factory, and there were girls, Jewish girls who were working there, went out every day was-- and Auschwitz was 3 kilometers from Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And little by little, these girls smuggled in the gunpowder-- tiny bits, bits by bits-- until they find the place, they find the route into the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I don't know that, because I heard from people that it's true.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The others, they don't know-- because so few survivors, that while the planning went on, as the partisans were in the forest, Polish and Jewish partisans-- and they were supposed to come out when the crematorium is blown up, come out and liberate Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Unfortunately, something went wrong.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "SS find out too early, and they were just waiting.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They watched what's happening.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when the crematorium blow up-- was blown up, it was in big flame-- they forced these sonderkommando, these people, to go into the burning building.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Of course, they refused.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they were shot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Nobody-- nobody survived from them-- as far as I know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then a few days later, we were just sent to the bathhouse, and was disinfected again-- gave us fresh clothes, and took us out to the railway station with a loaf of bread, and closed the door, and we were on-- we're on our way.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We didn't know that-- where to.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We never hoped that we will get out from there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they took us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "For about two days we traveled.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And in Berlin, the train stopped for a minute or so.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they took us in the siding.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
